  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason: The proposed development by reason of its inappropriate design, scale, massing and choice of finishing materials in this location would fail to bear any relationship to its surrounding context. The development would result in a loss of spaciousness and openness between the buildings along Camden Road and Beacon Hill to the detriment of the spacious character and appearance of the area and the wider Hillmarton Conservation Area. The development is therefore considered contrary to Islington's Unitary Development Plan policies D1 (Design), D3 (Design and Layout), D4 (Design in context), D5 (Townscape), D11 (Alterations and extensions) D24 (Materials), Hillmarton Conservation Guidance note 32, Islington's Urban design guidance 2006 and PPS 5."
